Program: Outlook
Title: Music Saved me From the Killing Fields
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0268cch
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 16 Sep 2014
Arn Chorn Pond survived a brutal childhood in Cambodia under the Khmer Rouge, but was eventually able to make a new life for himself in America. Now he's working to save traditional Cambodian art and music. Turkish film director Kutlug Ataman is recognised around the world for his documentaries. Italian Cesare Bergamini has been catching eels for four decades. His boathouse on the River Tiber is right under the Rome ringroad. Show less